cdx6500PPCTPadPortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTPadPortTable
cdx6500PPCTPadPortTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the Pad Port table.

cdx6500PPCTPadPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTPadPortEntry
cdx6500PPCTPadPortEntry.description: A row of Pad Port configuration parameters.

cdx6500padpCfgPortNum.name: cdx6500padpCfgPortNum
cdx6500padpCfgPortNum.description: Specifies the number of the port that you are configuring. This number also serves as an entry number for the port you are about to configure.

cdx6500padpCfgConnectionType.name: cdx6500padpCfgConnectionType
cdx6500padpCfgConnectionType.description: Specify the control signal handshake and clocking required for a connection to be made to this port: simp - simple, no control signals required. dtr - dedicated, require the data terminal ready signal (DTR). dtrd - same as DTR, except data set ready (DSR) drops between calls. dtrp - same as DTR, except DSR/DCD/CTS are held low in the idle state. dimo - port handshakes with attached dial modem. dimoa - same as DIMO except DSR never raised on incoming call from modem. dimob - same as DIMO except DSR follows DTR on incoming call from modem. emri - port emulates a dial modem with ring indicator (RI). emdc - port emulates a dial modem with data carrier detect (DCD). emdcio - port emulates a dial modem with DCD for incoming and outgoing calls. newvalSimp - same functionality as 'simp', new enumeration added for RFc1155 compatibility.

cdx6500padpCfgPortControl.name: cdx6500padpCfgPortControl
cdx6500padpCfgPortControl.description: Specify any of the following port control options: NONE - no option specified. MB - raise Pin 22 when the port becomes disabled.

cdx6500padpCfgPortSpeed.name: cdx6500padpCfgPortSpeed
cdx6500padpCfgPortSpeed.description: This is the speed of the port in bits per second (baud rate). newvalSpeed110 : same as 'speed110', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compliance.

cdx6500padpCfgAutoBaudSeq.name: cdx6500padpCfgAutoBaudSeq
cdx6500padpCfgAutoBaudSeq.description: This is the type of sequence used for autospeed detection on an autospeed port. crOnly - autospeed on <CR> crDotCr - autospeed on <CR>.<CR> tymnet - autospeed on a telenet - autospeed on <CR><CR> for 1200 baud or lower autospeed on @<CR> for 2400 baud or higher dotDotCr - autospeed on two or more dots followed by <CR> spacePCr - autospeed on <space>P<CR> newvalCrOnly - same functionality as 'crOnly', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500padpCfgDataBits.name: cdx6500padpCfgDataBits
cdx6500padpCfgDataBits.description: This is the number of data bits per character the PAD port expects when it transmits and receives data from the attached device.

cdx6500padpCfgParity.name: cdx6500padpCfgParity
cdx6500padpCfgParity.description: This is the parity the PAD port generates and expects when it transmits and receives data from the attached device. none - no parity space - Space Parity mark - Mark Parity even - Even Parity odd - Odd Parity auto - Auto Parity ( 7 odd / 7 even / 7 ignore ) autoA - Auto Parity ( 7 odd / 7 even / 8 none ). newvalNone - same functionality as 'none', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500padpCfgStopBits.name: cdx6500padpCfgStopBits
cdx6500padpCfgStopBits.description: This is the number of stop bits that the PAD port generates when it transmits data to the attached device. This parameter has no effect on data that is received from the attached device. stopBit1 - 1 Stop Bit. stopBit1p5 - 1.5 Stop Bits. stopBit2 - 2 Stop Bits. newvalStopBit1 - same functionality as 'stopBit1', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500padpCfgProfileName.name: cdx6500padpCfgProfileName
cdx6500padpCfgProfileName.description: This is the name of the PAD profile table to be used by this PAD port.

cdx6500padpCfgCallControl.name: cdx6500padpCfgCallControl
cdx6500padpCfgCallControl.description: This parameter allows call control to be used as follows: NONE - no option specified AUTO - automatic calling AUTC - automatic calling when carriage return received PCUD - pass call user data to user profiled for no service signals IBAR - bar calls inbound from PAD user OBAR - bar calls outbound to PAD user MNEM - allow mnemonic calls only EMNEM - allow extended mnemonic call (without DOT) Any combination of above specified by summing (e.g. AUTO+IBAR+. . .) TMNEM - Call Mnemonic (max 16 alphanumeric characters) which is not resolved in the local node. This option cannot be summed with any of the above.

cdx6500padpCfgTermControl.name: cdx6500padpCfgTermControl
cdx6500padpCfgTermControl.description: Specify options for the attached device: NONE - no option specified. PASS - require password entry to use this PAD facility. LIM - limit X.28 access to CALL and CLR commands only. CUG - check closed user group; otherwise, CUG passes transparently. LCPY - allow local copying to this PAD port. 7BIT - use 7 data bits for character processing. NADD - prevent PAD port from receiving calling address and FAC service signals. X28 - automatically return from X.28 mode to PAD mode after sending the X.28 commands. CNUI - Centralized NUI verification. CUGOA - check closed user group but allow outgoing access; otherwise, CUG passes transparently. BMSG - show the PAD Bulletin/Banner Message even if the PAD Profile #6 is configured as 1 or 5. ADDR - does not show the calling address HENNIS - supports Hanil bank terminal. FRCB - connect to a French Cartes Bancaires terminal CUGIA - check closed user group but allow incoming access; otherwise, CUG passes transparently.\r\n\ NO-NULL - If port speed is below or equal to 1200, null characters won't be appended to LF. BCUG-ON- Subscription to Bilateral Closed User Group facility enabled. BCUGOA - Subscription to Bilateral Closed User Group with Outgoing Access facility enabled. BCUG-OFF-Subscription to Bilateral Closed User Group related facilities disabled. BCUG-ON, BCUGOA and BCUG-OFF options are mutually exclusive. Any combination of above specified by summing (e.g. PASS+LIM).

cdx6500padpCfgPadPromptNum.name: cdx6500padpCfgPadPromptNum
cdx6500padpCfgPadPromptNum.description: This parameter specifies which entry in the PAD Prompt Table is used as a PAD prompt.

cdx6500padpCfgRemoteParamNum.name: cdx6500padpCfgRemoteParamNum
cdx6500padpCfgRemoteParamNum.description: This specifies which entry in the Remote PAD Parameters Table is sent to a remote PAD to update its X.3 characteristics when it connects to this port: 0 - no remote PAD update is performed.

cdx6500padpCfgAutoCallMnem.name: cdx6500padpCfgAutoCallMnem
cdx6500padpCfgAutoCallMnem.description: This mnemonic name is used if this port is configured for auto-calling.

cdx6500padpCfgAutoCallTimeout.name: cdx6500padpCfgAutoCallTimeout
cdx6500padpCfgAutoCallTimeout.description: This is the time interval in seconds between call attempts when auto-calling.

cdx6500padpCfgMaxAutoCall.name: cdx6500padpCfgMaxAutoCall
cdx6500padpCfgMaxAutoCall.description: This parameter is used to specify the number of times that the PAD port will attempt to call, when auto-calling is enabled. A value of zero, will allow unlimited attempts.

cdx6500padpCfgSubAddress.name: cdx6500padpCfgSubAddress
cdx6500padpCfgSubAddress.description: Calls addressed to this node and with this subaddress will be routed to this port.

cdx6500padpCfgGroupSubaddress.name: cdx6500padpCfgGroupSubaddress
cdx6500padpCfgGroupSubaddress.description: The group subaddress is shared by one or more ports. Calls addressed to this node and with this subaddress will be routed to a port within the group.

cdx6500padpCfgCugMembership.name: cdx6500padpCfgCugMembership
cdx6500padpCfgCugMembership.description: The port may be a member of up to 8 different Closed User Groups (CUGs). Each CUG membership must be a two digit number (except --) and separated by a comma. ( e.g. 12,34,56,09,02,03 ). -- - No CUG Membership 00-99 - CUG Membership

cdx6500padpCfgBillingRecord.name: cdx6500padpCfgBillingRecord
cdx6500padpCfgBillingRecord.description: This controls whether billing (accounting) records will be created for calls on this port. newvalOff : same functionality as 'off', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500padpCfgInviteToClr.name: cdx6500padpCfgInviteToClr
cdx6500padpCfgInviteToClr.description: This specifies the handling of Invitation to Clear packet when received. none - Do nothing. clrwo - Clear Call without performing a EIA disconnect. clrwd - Clear Call and perform a EIA disconnect. newvalNone - same functionality as 'none', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500padpCfgCallAcceptTime.name: cdx6500padpCfgCallAcceptTime
cdx6500padpCfgCallAcceptTime.description: Specifies the time (in seconds) that the user has to make a successful call, after a call has been cleared, before being automatically disconnected. A maximum of three call attempts are permitted when the Call Accept Timer is enabled. 1-255 - Call Accept Timeout (in seconds) 0 - Disables the Call Accept Timer.

cdx6500padpCfgProtectionLevel.name: cdx6500padpCfgProtectionLevel
cdx6500padpCfgProtectionLevel.description: This specifies the level of data or connection protection which will be applied to calls to or from this port. The actual level for a call will be negotiated to the lesser of this level and the level configured for the other end of the call. none - No protection cpOnly - Connection protection only fullDcp - Full data and connection protection. newvalNone - same functionality as 'none', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500padpCfgReconnectTimeout.name: cdx6500padpCfgReconnectTimeout
cdx6500padpCfgReconnectTimeout.description: This specifies the number of seconds that DCP on the originating side will wait between reconnection attempts.

cdx6500padpCfgReconnectTries.name: cdx6500padpCfgReconnectTries
cdx6500padpCfgReconnectTries.description: This specifies the number of times that DCP on the originating side will attempt to reconnect before clearing the call. If 0 is entered, it will not attempt to reconnect.

cdx6500padpCfgMaxRcvBufLength.name: cdx6500padpCfgMaxRcvBufLength
cdx6500padpCfgMaxRcvBufLength.description: This specifies the number of characters received by the driver before forwarding the packet. This parameter is configurable only for PAD ports of CPU+ cards. 1 - 128 : Value stored in MRBLR.

cdx6500padpCfgCommandLanguage.name: cdx6500padpCfgCommandLanguage
cdx6500padpCfgCommandLanguage.description: This specifies the language for PAD commands. ccitt : X.28 CCITT. dpn : DPN ITI. nc : Not configured.

cdx6500padpCfgNUIFacilityFormat.name: cdx6500padpCfgNUIFacilityFormat
cdx6500padpCfgNUIFacilityFormat.description: This parameter specifies the format of the NUI facility field. odpn : Specifies the old DPN format. ndpn : Specifies the new DPN format. dpn1992 : 1992 NUI format. nc : Not configured.

cdx6500padpCfgNUIVerifyTimer.name: cdx6500padpCfgNUIVerifyTimer
cdx6500padpCfgNUIVerifyTimer.description: Specify the NUI verification timer in seconds. The call is cleared when the timer expires.

cdx6500padpCfgMaxNUIViolations.name: cdx6500padpCfgMaxNUIViolations
cdx6500padpCfgMaxNUIViolations.description: The maximum number of successive NUI verification failures that can be tolerated when making verification attempts through a pad port.

cdx6500padpCfgActionTypeNUIV.name: cdx6500padpCfgActionTypeNUIV
cdx6500padpCfgActionTypeNUIV.description: This specifies the course of action to be taken if the NUI violations exceed the configured threshold count. This parameter is effective only if the Port Control parameter is set to CNUI. none : No action is taken . disc : Port is disconnected. degr : Port is busied-out for one minute then re-enabled. lock : Port is disabled. Operator intervention is required to enable the port. nc : Not configured.

cdx6500padpCfgCalledDTEAddress.name: cdx6500padpCfgCalledDTEAddress
cdx6500padpCfgCalledDTEAddress.description: Called DTE Address for packets with Call Mnemonic.

cdx6500padpCfgCallingDTEIdent.name: cdx6500padpCfgCallingDTEIdent
cdx6500padpCfgCallingDTEIdent.description: Calling DTE Identifier for packets with Call Mnemonic.

cdx6500padpCfgCallingDTEPasswd.name: cdx6500padpCfgCallingDTEPasswd
cdx6500padpCfgCallingDTEPasswd.description: Calling DTE Password for packets with Call Mnemonic.

cdx6500padpCfgX28ResetService.name: cdx6500padpCfgX28ResetService
cdx6500padpCfgX28ResetService.description: This is the name of the X.28 Reset Service Signals table to be used by this PAD port.

cdx6500padpCfgX28ClearService.name: cdx6500padpCfgX28ClearService
cdx6500padpCfgX28ClearService.description: This is the name of the X.28 Clear Service Signals table to be used by this PAD port.

cdx6500padpCfgMAXMNEMFailures.name: cdx6500padpCfgMAXMNEMFailures
cdx6500padpCfgMAXMNEMFailures.description: The maximum number of successive Mnemonic Call failures that can be tolerated when making a call to the remote using the mnemonic. This parameter is effective only if the Port Control parameter is set to MNEM.

cdx6500padpCfgActionTypeMNEMFail.name: cdx6500padpCfgActionTypeMNEMFail
cdx6500padpCfgActionTypeMNEMFail.description: This specifies the course of action to be taken if the Mnemonic exceed the configured threshold count. This parameter is effective only if the Port Control parameter is set to MNEM. none : No action is taken disc : Port is disconnected. degr : Port is busied-out for one minute then it is re-enabled. lock : Port is disabled. Operator intervention is required to enable the port. nc : Not configured.

cdx6500padpCfgActiveLineMessage.name: cdx6500padpCfgActiveLineMessage
cdx6500padpCfgActiveLineMessage.description: The message to be printed when the line becomes active (DTR goes high).

cdx6500padpCfgDelayActiveLine.name: cdx6500padpCfgDelayActiveLine
cdx6500padpCfgDelayActiveLine.description: When the line becomes active (DTR goes high), Active line message is sent after configured time. This delay is in seconds.

cdx6500padpCfgInterCharTimer.name: cdx6500padpCfgInterCharTimer
cdx6500padpCfgInterCharTimer.description: The maximum time period allowed between received characters in a frame. Specified in 50ms increments (i.e. 5 means 250ms).

cdx6500padpCfgElectricalInterfaceType.name: cdx6500padpCfgElectricalInterfaceType
cdx6500padpCfgElectricalInterfaceType.description: Specify the Electrical Interface Type: V.24 - V.24 Electrical Interface Type V.35 - V.35 Electrical Interface Type V.36 - V.36 Electrical Interface Type X.21 - X.21 Electrical Interface Type NONE - Electrically disabled

cdx6500padpCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOpti.name: cdx6500padpCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500padpCfgV24ElectricalInterfaceOpti.description: Specify the Pin 22 option: RI - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Ring Indicator output signal TM - V.24 uses Pin 22 for Test Mode input signal

cdx6500padpCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfa.name: cdx6500padpCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfaceOption
cdx6500padpCfgHighSpeedElectricalInterfa.description: Specify the cable type: NONE - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with straight through cable XOVER - V.35/V.36/X.21 DCE with crossover adapter cable

cdx6500PPSTPadPortTable.name: cdx6500PPSTPadPortTable
cdx6500PPSTPadPortTable.description: All of the statistics parameters relevant to the Pad Port table.

cdx6500PPSTPadPortEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTPadPortEntry
cdx6500PPSTPadPortEntry.description: A row of Pad Port statistics parameters.

cdx6500padpStatPortStatus.name: cdx6500padpStatPortStatus
cdx6500padpStatPortStatus.description: Status of the port: up - port is up and running. busyout - port has been busied out. disabled - port has been disabled. newvalDisabled : same functionality 'disabled', new new enumeration added RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500padpStatUtilizationIn.name: cdx6500padpStatUtilizationIn
cdx6500padpStatUtilizationIn.description: Percentage of port bandwidth in use.

cdx6500padpStatUtilizationOut.name: cdx6500padpStatUtilizationOut
cdx6500padpStatUtilizationOut.description: Percentage of port bandwidth in use.

cdx6500padpStatCharInTotal.name: cdx6500padpStatCharInTotal
cdx6500padpStatCharInTotal.description: Summary of the characters being received over the port.

cdx6500padpStatCharOutTotal.name: cdx6500padpStatCharOutTotal
cdx6500padpStatCharOutTotal.description: Summary of the characters being sent over the port.

cdx6500padpStatCharsInPerSec.name: cdx6500padpStatCharsInPerSec
cdx6500padpStatCharsInPerSec.description: Summary of the characters being received over the port.

cdx6500padpStatCharsOutPerSec.name: cdx6500padpStatCharsOutPerSec
cdx6500padpStatCharsOutPerSec.description: Summary of the characters being sent over the port.

cdx6500padpStatPktInTotal.name: cdx6500padpStatPktInTotal
cdx6500padpStatPktInTotal.description: Summary of the packets being sent over the port.

cdx6500padpStatPktOutTotal.name: cdx6500padpStatPktOutTotal
cdx6500padpStatPktOutTotal.description: Summary of the packets being sent over the port.

cdx6500padpStatPktsInPerSec.name: cdx6500padpStatPktsInPerSec
cdx6500padpStatPktsInPerSec.description: Summary of the packets being sent over the port.

cdx6500padpStatPktsOutPerSec.name: cdx6500padpStatPktsOutPerSec
cdx6500padpStatPktsOutPerSec.description: Summary of the packets being sent over the port.

cdx6500padpStatPktsQueued.name: cdx6500padpStatPktsQueued
cdx6500padpStatPktsQueued.description: Number of packets queued for output.

cdx6500padpStatOverrunErrors.name: cdx6500padpStatOverrunErrors
cdx6500padpStatOverrunErrors.description: Number of Overrun errors since the last reset.

cdx6500padpStatParityErrors.name: cdx6500padpStatParityErrors
cdx6500padpStatParityErrors.description: Number of Parity errors since the last reset.

cdx6500padpStatFramingErrors.name: cdx6500padpStatFramingErrors
cdx6500padpStatFramingErrors.description: Number of Framing errors since the last reset.

cdx6500padpStatCurrentStatus.name: cdx6500padpStatCurrentStatus
cdx6500padpStatCurrentStatus.description: Status of the call on the specific port (Disconnect, Calling, Called, Clearing, Connected, Local Copy)

cdx6500padpStatPortState.name: cdx6500padpStatPortState
cdx6500padpStatPortState.description: Current port state: x28 : The port is in Command mode. pad : The port is in Data mode. account : The port is waiting for the account name. password : The port is waiting for the password. newvalPad: same functionality as 'pad', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility. na : Value not available.

cdx6500CfgPadPromptTable.name: cdx6500CfgPadPromptTable
cdx6500CfgPadPromptTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the PAD Prompt table.

cdx6500CfgPadPromptEntry.name: cdx6500CfgPadPromptEntry
cdx6500CfgPadPromptEntry.description: A row of Pad Prompt table parameters

cdx6500padpromptEntryNum.name: cdx6500padpromptEntryNum
cdx6500padpromptEntryNum.description: This is not a configuration parameter. Instead, it identifies the particular PAD Prompt Table entry being configured by the other parameter in the record.

cdx6500padpromptPromptText.name: cdx6500padpromptPromptText
cdx6500padpromptPromptText.description: Enter PAD prompt as an ASCII character string, terminated by a carriage return. Use line feed (^j) to generate a new line. The prompt can have up to 1023 characters.

cdx6500CfgPadProfileTable.name: cdx6500CfgPadProfileTable
cdx6500CfgPadProfileTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the Pad Profile table.

cdx6500CfgPadProfileEntry.name: cdx6500CfgPadProfileEntry
cdx6500CfgPadProfileEntry.description: A row of Pad Profile configuration parameters

cdx6500padprofProfileNum.name: cdx6500padprofProfileNum
cdx6500padprofProfileNum.description: This is not a configuration parameter. Instead, it identifies the particular PAD Profile Table entry being configured by the other parameters in the record.

cdx6500padprofProfileName.name: cdx6500padprofProfileName
cdx6500padprofProfileName.description: Reference name for this PAD profile. Individual parameter prompt messages are prefixed with X.3 parameter number. Numbers greater than 100 indicate proprietary extensions.

cdx6500padprofPar1.name: cdx6500padprofPar1
cdx6500padprofPar1.description: #1, enables PAD recall to command mode during a call: 0 - PAD recall disabled 1 - PAD recall character = DLE = <^P> 32-126 - decimal value of character used for PAD recall

cdx6500padprofPar2.name: cdx6500padprofPar2
cdx6500padprofPar2.description: #2, controls echo: 0 - echo disabled 1 - echo enabled.

cdx6500padprofPar3.name: cdx6500padprofPar3
cdx6500padprofPar3.description: #3, selects the ASCII characters used for data forwarding: 0 - no data forwarding characters 1 - A-Z, a-z, 0-9 2 - CR 4 - ESC, BEL,ENQ, ACK 8 - DEL, CAN, DC2 16 - EOT, ETX 32 - HT, LF, VT, FF 64 - all characters in columns 0 and 1 of the ASCII table not mentioned above XXX - any combination of the above values.

cdx6500padprofPar4.name: cdx6500padprofPar4
cdx6500padprofPar4.description: #4, selects forwarding idle timer delay: 0 - idle timer disabled 1 to 255 - value of idle timer in 1/20 seconds.

cdx6500padprofPar5.name: cdx6500padprofPar5
cdx6500padprofPar5.description: #5, specifies whether the attached terminal is flow controlled (restrained from sending data) by the PAD port sending the XON, XOFF characters. Also called Data Restraint Inbound (DRI) using in-band control: 0 - no control with XON, XOFF 1 - control inbound data from device 2 - control inbound data and PAD commands from device For DRI control using V.24 connector control signals (CTS and pin 14), use parameter #105.

cdx6500padprofPar6.name: cdx6500padprofPar6
cdx6500padprofPar6.description: #6, controls PAD service signal messages to the attached device: 0 - no service signal is sent 1 - service signals, other than the prompt, are sent 4 - prompt service signal is sent 5 - all service signals are sent 9 - extended format service signals, other than prompt, are sent 12 - extended format prompt service signal is sent 13 - all service signals are sent in extended format.

cdx6500padprofPar7.name: cdx6500padprofPar7
cdx6500padprofPar7.description: #7, selects the PAD mode of operation on receipt of a break signal from the attached terminal: 0 - do nothing 1 - send Interrupt packet 2 - send Reset packet 4 - send Indication of Break packet 5 - send Interrupt packet and Indication of Break packet 8 - escape from data transfer state 21 - discard output, send Interrupt packet, and send Indication of Break Packet

cdx6500padprofPar9.name: cdx6500padprofPar9
cdx6500padprofPar9.description: #9, controls padding after carriage return (CR): 0 - no padding after CR. 1 to 255 - number of padding characters inserted after CR.

cdx6500padprofPar10.name: cdx6500padprofPar10
cdx6500padprofPar10.description: #10, controls line folding: 0 - no line folding. 1 to 255 - number of characters per line.

cdx6500padprofPar12.name: cdx6500padprofPar12
cdx6500padprofPar12.description: #12, specifies whether the PAD port is flow controlled (restrained from sending data) by the attached terminal sending the XON, XOFF characters. Also called Data Restraint Outbound (DRO) using in-band control: 0 - no control with XON, XOFF 1 - allow flow control on outbound data and service signals For DRO control using V.24 connector control signals (CTS and pin 14), use parameter #105.

cdx6500padprofPar13.name: cdx6500padprofPar13
cdx6500padprofPar13.description: #13, controls line feed insertion after carriage return (CR) in data transfer state: 0 - no line feed insertion 1 - after CR in data sent to attached device 2 - after CR in data from the attached device 4 - after echo of CR to attached device X - any combination of the above values.

cdx6500padprofPar14.name: cdx6500padprofPar14
cdx6500padprofPar14.description: #14, controls padding after line feed in the data transfer state: 0 - no padding after line feed 1 to 255 - number of padding characters inserted after line feed.

cdx6500padprofPar15.name: cdx6500padprofPar15
cdx6500padprofPar15.description: #15, controls local editing in data transfer state: 0 - no editing 1 - allow editing (idle timer data forwarding must be disabled, parameter #4 = 0) Editing is limited to deleting single characters, deleting the entered line and displaying the entered line.

cdx6500padprofPar16.name: cdx6500padprofPar16
cdx6500padprofPar16.description: #16, decimal value of ASCII character used to delete a character if editing is enabled (parameter #15 = 1).

cdx6500padprofPar17.name: cdx6500padprofPar17
cdx6500padprofPar17.description: #17, decimal value of ASCII character used to delete a line if editing is enabled (parameter #15 = 1).

cdx6500padprofPar18.name: cdx6500padprofPar18
cdx6500padprofPar18.description: #18, decimal value of ASCII character used to display a line if editing is enabled (parameter #15 = 1).

cdx6500padprofPar19.name: cdx6500padprofPar19
cdx6500padprofPar19.description: #19, specifies the type of character delete service signal sent by PAD: 0 - no service signal 1 - printing terminals (PAD sends \\ for each delete character received from terminal) 2 - display terminals (PAD sends <BS><SP><BS> for each delete character received from terminal) 8,32-126 - specifies the ASCII character used as the editing service signal.

cdx6500padprofPar20.name: cdx6500padprofPar20
cdx6500padprofPar20.description: #20, specifies the echo mask: 0 - no echo mask (all characters echoed) 1 - no echo of CR 2 - no echo of LF 4 - no echo of VT, HT, or FF 8 - no echo of BEL or BS 16 - no echo of ESC or ENQ 32 - no echo of ACK, NAK, STX, SOH, EOT, ETB, or ETX 64 - no echo of editing characters as designated by parameters 16, 17 and 18 128 - no echo of all other characters in columns 0 and 1 of the ASCII table not mentioned above and character DEL XXX - any combination of the above values.

cdx6500padprofPar21.name: cdx6500padprofPar21
cdx6500padprofPar21.description: #21, controls the parity treatment of characters received and transmitted to the attached device. 0 - No parity checking or generation 1 - Parity checked on received characters 2 - Parity generated in transmitted characters 4 - Parity stripped from received characters x - any combination of the above values.

cdx6500padprofPar22.name: cdx6500padprofPar22
cdx6500padprofPar22.description: #22, controls page wait: 0 - page wait disabled. 1 to 255 - number of line feed characters sent by the PAD for the page wait function.

cdx6500padprofPar100.name: cdx6500padprofPar100
cdx6500padprofPar100.description: #100, specifies the ASCII character used to simulate break for attached terminals that do not have a break key: 0 - no break character defined 1 to 127 - decimal value of the character used to simulate break.

cdx6500padprofPar101.name: cdx6500padprofPar101
cdx6500padprofPar101.description: #101, specifies the ASCII character used to toggle echo substitution of entered data. This function available only if parameter #2 = 1: 0 - no echo substitution function 1 to 127 - decimal value of character to use to toggle on and off the echo substitution.

cdx6500padprofPar102.name: cdx6500padprofPar102
cdx6500padprofPar102.description: #102, specifies the ASCII character used to echo all characters entered by the attached device when echo substitution is toggled on: 0 - no echo when echo substitution toggled on 1 to 127 - decimal value of character used as echo, if echoing is enabled by parameter #2 and substitution is enabled by parameter #101.

cdx6500padprofPar103.name: cdx6500padprofPar103
cdx6500padprofPar103.description: #103, specifies the ASCII character used for the XON function: 0 to 255 - decimal value of the XON character

cdx6500padprofPar104.name: cdx6500padprofPar104
cdx6500padprofPar104.description: #104, specifies the ASCII character used for the XOFF function: 0 to 255 - decimal value of the XOFF character.

cdx6500padprofPar105.name: cdx6500padprofPar105
cdx6500padprofPar105.description: #105, specifies whether both the PAD and the attached terminal are flow controlled (restrained from sending data) by the use of V.24 control signals, rather than XON, XOFF. This type of control is called out-of-band flow control. The control applies to data, commands and responses to and from an attached device: 0 - none using connector control signals 1 - Data Restraint Outbound, attached device flow controls PAD with connector pin 14 2 - Data Restraint Inbound, PAD flow controls attached device with connector pin 5, CTS X - any combination formed by summing (e.g. 1+2 or 3) For DRO control using XON/XOFF, use parameters #5 and #12.

cdx6500padprofPar106.name: cdx6500padprofPar106
cdx6500padprofPar106.description: #106, specifies parity of data sent to the network by the PAD: 0 - transparent - pass data as received 1 - space 2 - mark 3 - even 4 - odd

cdx6500padprofPar107.name: cdx6500padprofPar107
cdx6500padprofPar107.description: #107, is the elapsed time of no user data input after which a call on the port will be cleared: 0 - timer disabled 1 to 255 - timer value in minutes.

cdx6500padprofPar108.name: cdx6500padprofPar108
cdx6500padprofPar108.description: #108, specifies the ASCII character used to disconnect a call: 0 - no character disconnects the call. 1 to 127 - decimal value of call disconnect character.

cdx6500padprofPar109.name: cdx6500padprofPar109
cdx6500padprofPar109.description: #109, specifies the number of padding characters inserted in the data sent to the attached device after a form feed: 0 - no padding characters inserted. 1 to 255 - number of padding characters to insert after FF.

cdx6500padprofPar110.name: cdx6500padprofPar110
cdx6500padprofPar110.description: #110, Selects the data forwarding delay after ESC is detected 0 - timer disabled. 1 to 255 - timer value in 1/20 second.

cdx6500padprofPar111.name: cdx6500padprofPar111
cdx6500padprofPar111.description: #111, Controls how the pad handles the echo of data when echo, parameter 2, is on. 0 - No Priority. Data is output and characters are echoed as they arrive. 1 - Input Priority. PAD holds output until input from terminal is finished. 2 - Output Priority. PAD will reecho input after output. 3 - Formatted Screen. PAD will echo one block of data for each prompt sent from host.

cdx6500padprofPar112.name: cdx6500padprofPar112
cdx6500padprofPar112.description: #112, Setting this parameter causes the PAD port to dynamically forward data packets, as bandwidth becomes available on the network link. Settings for X.3 parameters 1,2,3,4,15,16,17,18,19,20,100,101, 102,106,108,110,111 and 13 value 2,3,6 or 7 are ignored if parameter 112 is set. 0 - Dynamic forwarding turned off. 1 - Dynamic forwarding turned on.

cdx6500padprofPar113.name: cdx6500padprofPar113
cdx6500padprofPar113.description: #113, Controls Hewlett-Packard flow control. 0 - No HP flow control. 1 - HP host enq/ack control. 2 - HP terminal enq/ack control. 3 - HP host xon/xoff control. 4 - HP terminal xon/xoff control.

cdx6500padprofPar114.name: cdx6500padprofPar114
cdx6500padprofPar114.description: #114, Selects PAD operational mode: 0 - Normal PAD. 1 - Transparent Polled Async Host PAD. 2 - Transparent Polled Async Remote PAD.

cdx6500padprofPar115.name: cdx6500padprofPar115
cdx6500padprofPar115.description: #115, Selects Data Forwarding Criteria for Polled Async PADs: 0 - Normal. 1 - Short Timer. 2 - RTS Signal Drop.

cdx6500padprofPar116.name: cdx6500padprofPar116
cdx6500padprofPar116.description: #116, Selects forwarding Short Timer duration for Polled Async PADs: 0 - Short Timer disabled. 1 to 255 - Duration of Short Timer in milliseconds.

cdx6500padprofPar117.name: cdx6500padprofPar117
cdx6500padprofPar117.description: #117, Selects EIA Signalling Action for Polled Async PADs: 0 - None. 1 - Raise DCD before transmission and drop DCD after transmission.

cdx6500padprofPar118.name: cdx6500padprofPar118
cdx6500padprofPar118.description: #118, Setting this parameter causes a Polled Async PAD to buffer complete async messages from the network before transmitting them to the attached device. 0 - Disabled. 1 - Enabled.

cdx6500padprofPar119.name: cdx6500padprofPar119
cdx6500padprofPar119.description: #119, This parameter specifies the amount of time that DCD is held high before data transmission to the attached device begins. This parameter is used when EIA Signalling Action (#117) is configured to 1. 0 - DCD to Data Timer disabled. 1 to 255 - Duration of DCD to Data Timer in milliseconds.

cdx6500CfgRemotePadTable.name: cdx6500CfgRemotePadTable
cdx6500CfgRemotePadTable.description: All of the configuration parameters relevant to the Remote Pad Paramter table.

cdx6500CfgRemotePadEntry.name: cdx6500CfgRemotePadEntry
cdx6500CfgRemotePadEntry.description: A row of Remote Pad configuration parameters

cdx6500remotepadEntryNum.name: cdx6500remotepadEntryNum
cdx6500remotepadEntryNum.description: This is not a configuration parameter. Instead, it identifies the particular PAD Parameter Table entry being configured by the other parameters in the record. This value is referenced by the parameter Remote PAD Parameter Number in the PAD Port Record.
